# =============================================================================
# Section 1 - ClawHavoc C2 IP PTR Lookups               :  6 rules 
# Section 2 - ClawHavoc Payload & Exfil Domains         :  6 rules 
# Section 3 - Supply Chain Fake Registry & Typosquats   :  2 rules 
# Section 4 - DNS Rebinding → CVE-2026-25253            :  5 rules
# Section 5 - mDNS Gateway Reconnaissance               :  3 rules 
# Section 6 - api.anthropic.com Typosquatting / MITM    :  2 rules 
# Section 7 - OpenClaw Instance Discovery Scan          :  1 rule  
# Section 8 - Enhanced Autoblock DNS Integration        :  9 rules [NEW v1.2.0]
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# TOTAL ACTIVE RULES                                    : 34 rules
# =============================================================================
#
# CONFIGURATION NOTES:
#   1. Define $DNS_SERVERS in suricata.yaml to enable rule 9203923:
#        vars:
#          address-groups:
#            DNS_SERVERS: "[8.8.8.8, 8.8.4.4, 1.1.1.1, 1.0.0.1]"
#
#   2. For Section 4 (DNS rebinding), ensure your internal DNS servers
#      are in $HOME_NET so that legitimate RFC1918 responses from internal
#      resolvers are NOT flagged (they come from $HOME_NET:53, not
#      $EXTERNAL_NET:53, so they are excluded by rule direction).
#
#   3. Rule 9203908 (glot.io), 9203909 (webhook.site), 9203910 (pipedream.net),
#      and 9100015 (ngrok.io) use threshold:type both with a count > 1 to
#      prevent false positives from legitimate developer use. Adjust thresholds
#      per your environment's expected usage patterns.
#
#   4. All Section 1 rules (PTR lookups for C2 IPs) have ZERO false positive
#      risk — these exact IP addresses have no legitimate use and are confirmed
#      ClawHavoc C2 infrastructure.
#
#   5. Rule 9203906 (socifiapp.com) and 9203907 (install.app-distribution.net)
#      also have effectively ZERO false positive risk — these domains were
#      purpose-built for this malware campaign and have no legitimate traffic.
#
